data(brfss_smart2010)  
brfss_smart2010 = janitor::clean_names(brfss_smart2010) %>% 
filter(topic == "Overall Health") %>%
mutate(response = forcats::fct_relevel(response, c("Excellent", "Good", "Very good", "Fair", "Poor")))
year_2002 = filter(brfss_smart2010, year == 2002)%>%
group_by(locationdesc,locationabbr) %>% group_by(locationabbr) %>% summarize(n=n()/5)  ##7 locations observed


year_2002_2010 = brfss_smart2010 %>%
group_by(locationdesc,locationabbr, year) %>% group_by(locationabbr, year) %>%
summarize(n=n()/5)

ggplot(year_2002_2010, aes(x = year, y = n, color = locationabbr)) + 
    geom_line() +

Question 3

a = ny_noaa %>% 
    group_by(id, month) %>%
  filter(month == "01"|month == "07") %>%
   mutate(tmax_F = as.numeric(tmax_F, na.rm=TRUE)) %>%
  summarize(mean_tmax_F = mean(tmax_F)) %>% 
  na.omit(mean_tmax_F)

 ggplot(a, aes(x =id, y = mean_tmax_F)) + 
  geom_point(alpha = .5) +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE) +
   facet_grid(~month)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

 ggplot(a, aes(x = month, y = mean_tmax_F)) + 
  geom_boxplot() 

 ##Make a two-panel plot showing the average max temperature
b = ny_noaa %>% 
  na.omit(tmin_F)%>%
  na.omit(tmin_F) %>%
  mutate(tmax_F = as.numeric(tmax_F, na.rm=TRUE)) %>%
   mutate(tmin_F = as.numeric(tmin_F, na.rm=TRUE)) 
  ggplot(b, aes(x = tmax_F, y = tmin_F)) + 
  geom_hex()

##Make a two-panel plot showing (i) tmax vs tmin for the full dataset (note that a scatterplot may not be the best option); and (ii) make a plot showing the distribution of snowfall values greater than 0 and less than 100 separately by year.
  c = ny_noaa %>% 
  na.omit(snow_in) %>%
  mutate(snowfall = as.numeric(snow_in, na.rm=TRUE)) %>%
  filter(snowfall>0,snowfall<100) 
  ggplot(c, aes(x = snowfall, fill = year)) + 
  geom_density()

The size of the data set is 2595176, 9 The key variables of the original data set are id,date, snow, tmax, and tmin. There are missing data in variable “prcp”, “snow”, “snwd”, “tmax”, and “tmin”. Among these variables, “tmax” and “tmin” have the largest number of missing values.

library(ggplot2)
library(patchwork)
ggplot(b, aes(x = tmax_F, y = tmin_F)) + 
  geom_hex() + ggplot(c, aes(x = snowfall, fill = year)) + 
  geom_density()

(2)From the scatterplot, the mean max temperature of january is around zero F, and the mean max temperature of july is around 300F.From the boxplot, we observe there are two outliers in july: one is below average and one is above average. 3(i) From the plot on the left, the value of tmin and tmax occur most around zero. (ii) From the plot on the right, the density is largest when the value of snowfall is zero. Also, the density of snow fall is gerally decreasing with the increasing value snowfall.
